    <!-- FAQ Questions & Answers -->
    <string name="faq_prayer_times_q">How are prayer times calculated?</string>
    <string name="faq_prayer_times_a">Prayer times are calculated using your location and the calculation method you select in Prayer Settings. Different methods are used by different regions and Islamic organizations.</string>
    <string name="faq_mosque_difference_q">Why are my prayer times different from my local mosque?</string>
    <string name="faq_mosque_difference_a">Different mosques may use different calculation methods or manual adjustments. You can change your calculation method in Prayer Settings, or use per-prayer time adjustments.</string>
    <string name="faq_set_location_q">How do I set my location?</string>
    <string name="faq_set_location_a">Go to More > Prayer Settings > Location. You can search for your city or use GPS to detect your current location automatically.</string>
    <string name="faq_qibla_q">How does the Qibla compass work?</string>
    <string name="faq_qibla_a">The Qibla compass uses your phone\'s magnetometer and GPS location to calculate the direction of the Kaaba in Makkah. Make sure to calibrate your compass by moving your phone in a figure-8 pattern.</string>
    <string name="faq_track_prayers_q">Can I track my prayers?</string>
    <string name="faq_track_prayers_a">Yes! Tap on any prayer time on the home screen to mark it as prayed. You can view your prayer history and streaks in Prayer Stats.</string>
    <string name="faq_quran_translation_q">How do I change the Quran translation?</string>
    <string name="faq_quran_translation_a">Go to More > App Settings > Quran Settings (or the Quran tab) and select your preferred translator.</string>
    <string name="faq_notifications_q">Why am I not receiving notifications?</string>
    <string name="faq_notifications_a">Make sure notifications are enabled in the app (More > Notifications) and in your device\'s system settings. Also check that battery optimization is disabled for Nimaz.</string>
    <string name="faq_tasbih_q">How do I use the Tasbih counter?</string>
    <string name="faq_tasbih_a">Go to the Tasbih tab, select a preset or create your own, and tap the counter to increment. You can set a target count and the app will notify you when reached.</string>

